    <section class="section">
      <h2>Current Status</h2>
      <p>As of May 2026, the auto-trading project has moved past the order-execution stabilization stage and entered the regime-based strategy engine validation stage.</p>
      <p>The May 11, 2026 upgrade introduced a KOSPI 5-day return regime detection system. The strategy engine now switches MA20 deviation thresholds based on BULL / NEUTRAL / BEAR market regime, resolving the structural problem where a fixed 5% ceiling was blocking leading stocks during surges.</p>
      <p><strong>Core of this upgrade</strong></p>
      <ul class="gains-list">
        <li>KOSPI 5-day return based BULL / NEUTRAL / BEAR regime detection</li>
        <li>Dynamic MA20 deviation ceiling: BULL 8% / NEUTRAL 5% / BEAR 3%</li>
        <li>Universe expanded from 20 to 40 candidates</li>
        <li>11:00 BULL-only buy cycle added</li>
        <li>Pullback filter added (OR structure with MA20 deviation)</li>
        <li>RSI ceiling raised from 65 to 70 (RSI 75 chase-block kept)</li>
        <li>Partial profit-taking: 50% exit at +6%, remainder on trailing stop</li>
        <li>Tiered trailing: +4–8% at -2.5% / +8–15% at -2.0% / +15%+ at -1.5%</li>
        <li>Daily buy limit raised from 2 to 3</li>
        <li>Settlement-price pnl tracking and consolidated sell alerts</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Next validation (1–2 weeks of live logs)</strong></p>
      <ul class="gains-list">
        <li>Buy frequency by regime: does BULL regime actually produce more buys?</li>
        <li>Pullback entry performance: risk-reward comparison vs MA20 deviation entries</li>
        <li>Partial profit-taking effect: final return vs full-position trailing</li>
        <li>Overall risk-reward improvement</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="timeline-cta"><a href="/en/log/2026-05-11-auto-trading-regime-upgrade/">Regime Upgrade Log →</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/en/insight/insight-032/">Related Insight →</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/en/log/2026-05-08-auto-trading-strategy-engine-first-refinement/">Previous Engine Refinement Log →</a></p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>The Problem Being Solved</h2>
      <p>Can a non-coder build and operate a real automated trading system by collaborating with AI?</p>
      <p>The operator handles <strong>judgment</strong>. AI handles <strong>execution</strong>. The question is whether this division of roles holds up when real capital is on the line. The current ₩10M-level structure is the answer in progress.</p>
      <p>The goal is not profit. The goal is the experience of building a system where AI operates real capital — by hand, from scratch.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Structure and How It Works</h2>
      <p>Three roles. The operator (철부지) sets strategy direction and makes final calls. GPT (메타철부지) handles strategy design and research. Claude Code handles code analysis and modification. KIS API (Korea Investment Securities) executes orders on the live account.</p>
      <p>Buy decisions run through a rule engine. RSI momentum, MA20 deviation, market regime (5-condition scoring), RS filter, and sector overlap limits are checked before candidates are sorted by strength and scanned 3 times per day (10:00 / 13:00 / 14:00). The current stop-loss baseline is -2.5%, the target profit baseline is +5.0%, and trailing stop activation is based on +4%.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Key Achievements</h2>
      <ul class="achievements">
        <li><strong>MVP to live account in 20 days</strong> (2026-04-07 → 2026-04-20)</li>
        <li><strong>1-week paper trade result:</strong> +₩45,060 (+0.58%) — used as the basis for evaluating the live switch</li>
        <li><strong>First live order:</strong> 2026-04-14 Kakao 20 shares @ ₩48,350</li>
        <li><strong>Current operating structure:</strong> total-asset-ratio-based allocation at roughly the ₩10M seed level</li>
        <li><strong>Strategy engine first refinement:</strong> -2.5% stop-loss, +5.0% target profit, 20% cash buffer, sector overlap limit, profit-risk analysis log placement</li>
        <li><strong>Strategy shift:</strong> "fill all slots" → "hold only strong candidates, keep cash otherwise" (RS filter)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

